    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ARRESTS IN PLOT AGAINST EGG</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Three men are arrested and accused of plotting a heist in cyberspace to rob Egg PLC, Britain's biggest stand-alone Internet bank; Egg, which has 1.1 million customers and is 80 percent owned by Prudential PLC, denies newspaper report it lost money and says it has installed software to help police track down hackers (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>British police officials said three men had been arrested and accused of plotting a heist in cyberspace to rob Egg P.L.C., the country's biggest stand-alone Internet bank. Egg, which has 1.1 million customers and is 80 percent owned by the insurer Prudential P.L.C., denied a newspaper report that it had lost money and said it had installed software to help the police track down the hackers. Some investors have expressed worries about security at Web banks.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
